1
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:34,000
***

2
00:01:10,640 --> 00:01:12,437
David!

3
00:01:14,600 --> 00:01:16,636
David!

4
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,800
David!

5
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:28,996
<i> I love you, Joseph. </ i></i>

6
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,393
Hey, I can wait out here all day.

7
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,472
Jesus.

8
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:06,594
Your last book sold 5 million copies.
Surely you could've done better than this.

9
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:14,669
Glad to see that you're writing again.

10
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:18,076
Yeah, well there have never been a problem
with that, I write every day.

11
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:20,589
- So, what is the problem?
- I'm done.

12
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:23,600
This doesn't look like you're done.
This looks like a bestseller.

13
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:25,325
That's not even a book. It's personal.

14
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:28,200
All your writing is personal.
That's why it sells.

15
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:31,357
I write dime store thrillers,
so spare me the pretense.

16
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:34,840
You have a legion of followers that would disagree with you.

17
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:35,860
What's this?

18
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,640
That's none of your concern.

19
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:50,194
- It's just a diary.
- An autobiography?

20
00:03:50,195 --> 00:03:51,195
It's a diary!

21
00:03:51,196 --> 00:03:54,999
I'm part of this support group,
and now we write about our pain.

22
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,669
You know, your writing is a lot more
important than you may think.

23
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:04,314
I can't begin to fathom what you must be going through.

24
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,840
I'm fine.

25
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,073
Stop punishing yourself Joe.

26
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:12,953
You've got to get out of this room.

27
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,518
I miss you.

28
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:43,560
<i>The day that Sarah and David died,</ i></i>

29
00:04:43,640 --> 00:04:46,680
<i>So did my faith in that there was
some sort of higher power.</ i></i>

30
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:50,080
<i>There's no divine beings and a master architect.</ i></i>

31
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,160
<i>Surely no deity could be responsible for so much pain, </ i></i>

32
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,680
<i>so much fucking misery.</ i></i>

33
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:59,080
<i> God is dead.
Or maybe he was never alive.</ I></i>

34
00:05:07,680 --> 00:05:12,800
All my friends had these, careers,
and I just had a job.

35
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:17,600
It didn't matter. When I met Henry,
everything changed.

36
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:23,480
I quit my job ... and I was a wife.

37
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,800
Full time.

38
00:05:26,280 --> 00:05:29,040
I was the most important thing in his life.

39
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:35,276
He needed me and he was the only family I ever had.

40
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,473
And I was good.

41
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,600
No, I was great.

42
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:43,760
When he died,

43
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,200
I died too.

44
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,800
I never realized the importance of family,

45
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:54,000
until the one I had was taken away.

46
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:57,840
But now, I wake up every morning ...

47
00:05:59,160 --> 00:06:03,200
I write my journal ...
and I know that tomorrow is a new day.

48
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:27,120
Don't loose those.
High street value and all that.

49
00:06:27,121 --> 00:06:28,119
Yeah.

50
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:31,669
- You know you're up?
- I don't think that's gonna happen.

51
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:35,588
- Why not?
- I just don't have very much to say.

52
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:39,110
You've been coming here for months
and you've not said a thing.

53
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:42,198
I'm pretty sure you have an encyclopedia
of things to say.

54
00:06:43,560 --> 00:06:47,348
- At least I see you're following the steps.
- Oh yeah.

55
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:53,276
No it's just ... I don't wanna go in there
and just bore everybody.

56
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:58,118
My story ends the same as everybody else's,
in Tragedy.

57
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:04,272
You know for someone so good with words ...

58
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:07,480
I find it hard to believe you can't find the
right ones to share.

59
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:14,360
You shouldn't look so surprised.
I read quite a lot you know.

60
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,040
Yeah, sorry.

61
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:55,320
Hey, um ... seems a bit stupid now, but I read
somewhere that you don't like using computers.

62
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:58,671
And I saw your tattered notebooks in group, so ...

63
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:02,715
- I know it's lame.
- Wow, thanks! It's not lame, it's great.

64
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:05,880
Okay, bye!

65
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,520
Call 911!

66
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:49,156
<i>Joseph.</i>

67
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:58,469
Mr. Crone?
Mr. Crone, can you hear me?

68
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:05,280
- You're one very lucky man.
- Am I?

69
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:09,200
Yes you are. You are in St. Luke's hospital now.

70
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,720
Mr. Crone, do you remember what happened?

71
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,500
Yeah.

72
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:17,079
I do not know who your guardian angel is,

73
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:19,360
but you might consider giving him a raise.

74
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:24,400
- The other driver?
- He didn't have your luck.

75
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:43,040
Can I come in?

76
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:47,237
Sorry, I can leave.
I just didn't know who to call or ....

77
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:50,909
- There's no one to call.
- Looks like you're gonna need a new watch.

78
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:56,550
I get to bed every night praying I won't
wake up in the morning.

79
00:09:56,800 --> 00:10:00,236
I pray I walk out of the house and get
struck by lightning.

80
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:03,591
I pray to a God I know doesn't exist to run me down by car,

81
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:06,359
and the day it finally happens I walk away
without a scratch.

82
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:09,392
- It wasn't your time.
- No it is my time, I have no purpose.

83
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:14,514
You're a famous author, with legions of fans.
Your books inspire millions of people.

84
00:10:14,640 --> 00:10:17,916
- But you have no purpose?
- This is not group therapy. Okay?

85
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:23,031
Look. I know what it's like to feel sorry for
yourself, and it's dangerous.

86
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:27,199
I used to be alone and have no reason to ...
- Yeah, I know, you found God.

87
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:31,791
No. I met someone who showed me something
that changed my outlook on the world.

88
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:33,440
We all have our purpose.

89
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:36,800
Just because you feel alone,
it doesn't mean you've lost yours.

90
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:40,911
- How you're getting home?
- Taking a cab.

91
00:10:42,760 --> 00:10:44,200
No you're not.

92
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:47,920
I'll get the car and meet you outside.

93
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,440
Do not answer the call, Joseph.

94
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,640
They are watching you.

95
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:16,400
But do not answer their call.

96
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:22,840
Will I see you at group tomorrow?
I can give you a lift if you like.

97
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:25,600
That's probably a good idea considering
my driving skills

98
00:11:26,160 --> 00:11:27,760
See you.

99
00:11:31,680 --> 00:11:32,840
Joseph.

100
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,960
Don't forget this.

101
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:38,261
Hey ...

102
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:42,035
I just wanted to say thank you for being there for me.

103
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,800
And thanks for this!

104
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,600
Bye!

105
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:14,600
Shit.
Hello?

106
00:12:16,401 --> 00:12:17,401
Hello?

107
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:19,800
<i>Joseph?</ i></i>

108
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:24,720
How'd you get this number?

109
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,200
<i>Dad's dying.</ i></i>

110
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:31,520
<i>The hospital released him to spend his
last days at home.</ i></i>

111
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:35,400
<i>I don't expect you to come,
I just thought you should know.</ i></i>

112
00:12:57,080 --> 00:13:00,600
<i>Barcelona, Spain</ i></i>

113
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:25,280
That address is 45 minutes from Barcelona.

114
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,556
It's a very expensive trip.

115
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:31,593
- I'm sorry, I don't speak Spanish.
- No, no. English.

116
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:54,160
<i>Returning to Spain brings back so many memories.</ i></i>

117
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,760
<i>Things I never wanted to revisit</ i></i>

118
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:04,160
<i>My old man ... his faith.
A God that abandoned me.</ I></i>

119
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:08,680
<i>My brother, who ...
although we have the same blood,</ i></i>

120
00:14:08,760 --> 00:14:10,320
<i>remains a stranger to me.</ i></i>

121
00:14:49,880 --> 00:14:51,000
Hello?

122
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:01,360
Hello?

123
00:16:22,880 --> 00:16:25,400
You must be Joseph.

124
00:16:28,800 --> 00:16:30,880
- And you are?
- My name is Anna.

125
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,200
So, you are a famous writer?

126
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,834
I don't like your books.
I only believe in one book.

127
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:42,320
Well, I'm taking care of your father until he passes.

128
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:46,400
I will give you some time to be with him.

129
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:19,920
They're watching, Joseph.

130
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:22,720
They're coming for him.

131
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:27,120
You must save him.

132
00:17:27,480 --> 00:17:30,800
Are you ready to save him, boy?

133
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:34,960
- I understand what you're talking about.
- He needs your help.

134
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:37,720
Dad, I don't know what you're trying to tell me.

135
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:40,960
He cannot do this by himself.

136
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:43,320
I'm gonna get Anna, for you.

137
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:46,560
It's good to see you son.

138
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,600
Joseph?

139
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:09,800
I can't believe it.
You made it.

140
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:13,520
- I'm not staying, I can't be here.
- What? Where are you going?

141
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,600
- Hotel.
- A hotel?

142
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:20,319
Joe, I read online you were in a car accident.
You didn't even call us.

143
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:22,670
- What could you have done?
- Been there for you.

144
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,500
We've never been there for each other.

145
00:18:24,501 --> 00:18:27,079
Not when we were kids, and you're not
gonna be there for me now.

146
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:30,993
That could change. We've changed.
The lord has a plan for you brother.

147
00:18:31,120 --> 00:18:33,680
The lords plan hasn't quite worked out for me has it?

148
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:35,320
Do you resent us that much?

149
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:40,000
I don't resent you Samuel.
I resent what you represent.

150
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:43,749
What he represents,
what this whole place represents.

151
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:49,315
They do not think he'll make it past the week.
I do not think he'll make it past the night.

152
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:52,956
So whatever hatred you have for the church,
don't take it out on us.

153
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:57,358
Please.
Stay the night.

154
00:19:08,280 --> 00:19:11,989
- So what happened to your church?
- Congregation dwindled.

155
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:14,475
More and more lost their faith.

156
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:18,593
We hope to find a new place as soon as the
messages from our sermon spread.

157
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:21,360
Perhaps you can lend us some of your loyal readers to the cause.

158
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,520
Yeah ... What cause is that?

159
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:26,720
Transcending the world's perception of religion.

160
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:29,440
Yeah, I don't know if my readers would be
buying what you're selling.

161
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:32,120
You'd be surprised what your fans would believe in.

162
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:38,637
You know why mom bought this thing
when we moved to Spain?

163
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:42,389
To remind us that angels are all around us.

164
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:46,752
Ever since Sarah and David died,
this statue's been in my nightmares.

165
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,240
It won't bite you.

166
00:19:48,360 --> 00:19:51,440
It just reminds me of things I'd like to forget.

167
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,880
I have something for you.

168
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:10,836
I wish I could say I've read them all.
Seems as soon as I'm reading one, two more come out.

169
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:14,077
Do you really have as little faith as the
characters in your books?

170
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:15,716
Maybe less.

171
00:20:15,717 --> 00:20:18,817
An atheist and a pastor.
We're quite the pair aren't we?

172
00:20:19,960 --> 00:20:24,431
- Do you still write every day?
- Yeah, it's actually the only thing I inherited from him.

173
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:25,840
Me too.

174
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:30,560
For the past few Christmases and birthdays we've missed.

175
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:33,433
Please, I want you to have this.

176
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:43,470
- For continued success with the writing.
- You didn't have to do this.

177
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:47,195
It's been too long, brother.
It's good to see you.

178
00:20:57,280 --> 00:21:00,955
Last few months we've had ongoing issues with vandals.

179
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:05,551
We installed those around the compound,
more than anything just to act as a deterrent.

180
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:08,991
<i>- Catch any bad guys?
- We caught something.</i>

181
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:25,151
- Anna has a very vivid imagination.
- Come, Joseph, come.

182
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:34,949
- What is this?
- Each camera takes one picture per minute,

183
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:38,311
unless the motion sensor is triggered and it rolls video.

184
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:41,350
This is from last week.

185
00:21:51,840 --> 00:21:53,239
There.

186
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:57,079
Look!

187
00:21:58,800 --> 00:21:59,920
What?

188
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:02,160
A demon.

189
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:12,230
- That's fog.
- My brother he ... he lacks faith.

190
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:14,200
I don't lack faith. I have faith.

191
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:18,600
I have faith in what makes rational sense.
God, and demons, and the devil don't.

192
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,720
I am going to pray for you.

193
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,440
- George Washington.
- What about him?

194
00:22:25,441 --> 00:22:27,640
Have you ever met him?
Have you ever met anyone who's ever met him?

195
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:32,120
No. No pictures, nothing. Only text.
Yet you still believe in George Washington.

196
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:37,040
God is a myth, Samuel. Neither you nor
Washington is gonna convince me otherwise.

197
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:45,958
David died at 11:11.
The time on his death certificate.

198
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:52,070
Not a number you easily forget.
I've been seeing that number a lot lately.

199
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:22,760
Hello?

200
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:25,000
I got your number from the hospital,
I hope that's okay.

201
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,080
The hospital gave you my number?

202
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:32,240
<i>Well, I didn't say they gave me the number.
I said that I got from the hospital.</i>

203
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:35,120
<i>You know, I waited outside your hotel
for 30 minutes.</ i></i>

204
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:38,400
Yeah, I'm sorry.
I ... I forgot.

205
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:42,877
- I had a little bit of an emergency.
- An emergency, on top of the accident?

206
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:46,879
- You're having quite the week.
- I'm having quite a year.

207
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,200
- I'm in Spain.
- What?

208
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,120
<i> Yeah, I'm in Barcelona.</ i></i>

209
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:55,040
<i>- You're serious?
- Yes, my brother and my father live here.</i>

210
00:23:55,280 --> 00:23:59,068
- My father moved here when I was a little kid.
- I'm so happy you're with your family, Joseph.

211
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:01,350
I wanna ask you a question.

212
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:07,392
You ever see a number reappearing in your life
over and over again?

213
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:10,718
- Such as?
- 11:11.

214
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:18,951
- Well. Did you make a wish?
- A wish?

215
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:23,194
Yeah. You know, when you look up and see
a clock that says 11:11 and you make a wish.

216
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:27,069
- No, why?
- An old wives tale, it's lucky I think.

217
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,872
Why are you asking me this?

218
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:36,439
<i>Why am I back here? Why am I staying when
everything in my being is telling me to run?</ i></i>

219
00:24:36,560 --> 00:24:40,235
<i>I remember the day we moved into this house
and how much I hated it.</ i></i>

220
00:24:40,360 --> 00:24:43,672
<i>How much I hated my father for moving us here.</ i></i>

221
00:24:43,673 --> 00:24:44,873
<i>How I resented him.</i>

222
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:51,188
<i>Not much has changed.
I still feel like an outsider.</i>

223
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:53,675
<i>Even amongst my own family.</ i></i>

224
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:28,000
Anna?

225
00:25:34,677 --> 00:25:35,677
Anna?

226
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,389
<i> Diary of Anne. </ i></i>

227
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:36,640
I'm afraid I am not at good at writing as you.

228
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:41,800
- I am very sorry. I was just curious.
- It's okay.

229
00:26:43,320 --> 00:26:48,240
- So you're a writer.
- It's a gospel, according to me.

230
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:52,436
I don't read Spanish, but it looks like a diary.

231
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:54,796
A record of my faith.

232
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:59,834
You know, if I kept a record of my faith,
it would be a book with no pages.

233
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:05,111
I keep a diary.

234
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:08,831
I know. But this is mine.

235
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:14,195
Something your father encouraged of his congregation.

236
